<h2 id="chapter-3-electromagnetic-energy">Chapter 3: Electromagnetic Energy</h2>

<p>Stuff from 8.02.</p>

<script type="math/tex; mode=display">C = \frac{\epsilon A}{d}</script>

<script type="math/tex; mode=display">E_{EM} = \frac{1}{2} C V^2</script>

<script type="math/tex; mode=display">P_{resistance} = \frac{V^2 (t)}{R}</script>

<script type="math/tex; mode=display">R = \frac{\rho l}{A}</script>

<p>Resistive Losses over a Transmission line:</p>

<script type="math/tex; mode=display">\frac{P_{lost}}{P_{L}} \approx \frac{R P_L}{V_{RMS}^{2}}</script>

<h2 id="chapter-4-waves-and-light">Chapter 4: Waves and Light</h2>

<p>Wave equation:</p>

<script type="math/tex; mode=display">\frac{\delta^2 f}{\delta t^2} = v^2 \frac{\delta^2 f}{\delta x^2}</script>

